thief: We defeated the Horrible Thing at the Centre of the Universe and all I got was a stupid badge. I tried to inherit from two parent classes at once, but Java does not support multiple inheritance with classes!
thief: What's in the chest? Well, what I stole is another matter! Heh[pause=0.2!] heh[pause=0.2!] heh[pause=0.2!]... In java, we can achieve multiple inheritance only through Interfaces.
if {HasThiefToken} == 0:
	thief: You want [b]what[/b]? An autograph? Do you know what parchment costs these days?
	thief: Take this trinket instead. Don't say I never did anything for you.
	[signal arg="coin_received"]
	set {HasThiefToken} = 1
	set {TokenCount} += 1
[end_timeline]